00104 /* The default prefetcher stats printing function. */
00105 void
00106 prefetch_t::reg_stats(
00107     struct stat_sdb_t * const sdb,
00108     const struct core_t * const core)
00109 {
00110   char buf[256];
00111   char buf2[256];
00112   char buf3[256];
00113   char core_str[256];
00114 
00115   if(core == NULL)
00116     core_str[0] = 0; /* empty string */
00117   else
00118     sprintf(core_str,"c%d.",core->current_thread->id);
00119 
00120   sprintf(buf,"%s%s.%s.bits",core_str,cp->name,type);
00121   sprintf(buf2,"total size of %s in bits",type);
00122   stat_reg_int(sdb, true, buf, buf2, &bits, bits, NULL);
00123   sprintf(buf,"%s%s.%s.size",core_str,cp->name,type);
00124   sprintf(buf2,"total size of %s in KB",type);
00125   sprintf(buf3,"%s%s.%s.bits / 8192.0",core_str,cp->name,type);
00126   stat_reg_formula(sdb, true, buf, buf2, buf3, NULL);
00127   sprintf(buf,"%s%s.%s.lookups",core_str,cp->name,type);
00128   sprintf(buf2,"number of prediction lookups in %s",type);
00129   stat_reg_counter(sdb, true, buf, buf2, &lookups, lookups, NULL);
00130 }

00152 #define PREFETCH_PARSE_ARGS
00153 /*====================================================*/
00154 /* argument parsing                                   */
00155 /*====================================================*/
00156   struct prefetch_t *
00157 prefetch_create(const char * const opt_string, struct cache_t * const cp)
00158 {
00159   char type[256];
00160 
00161   /* the format string "%[^:]" for scanf reads a string consisting of non-':' characters */
00162   if(sscanf(opt_string,"%[^:]",type) != 1)
00163     fatal("malformed prefetch option string: %s",opt_string);
00164 
00165   if(!strcasecmp(type,"none"))
00166     return NULL;
00167   
00168   /* include the argument parsing code.  PREFETCH_PARSE_ARGS is defined to
00169      include only the parsing code and not the other prefetcher code. */
00170 #include "ZCOMPS-prefetch.list"
00171 
00172 
00173   /* UNKNOWN prefetch Type */
00174   fatal("Unknown prefetcher type (%s)",opt_string);
00175 }
00176 
00177 #undef PREFETCH_PARSE_ARGS
